text: Walberswick is a village and civil parish in Suffolk Coastal, Suffolk, England. In 2001 there were 299 people living in Walberswick. Walberswick has a church called St Andrew. Walberswick is on the south bank of the River Blyth. == References == * GENUKI Category:Villages in Suffolk Category:Civil parishes in Suffolk Category:Suffolk Coastal
